.TH BOOKGEN 1 "April 2026" "bookgen 1.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
bookgen \- chapter-by-chapter long-form generator for Ollama/OpenAI APIs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bookgen
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fIFILES...\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
BookGen generates long-form content chapter-by-chapter, summarizes each chapter
for continuity, and writes chapter and full-book outputs to disk.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-S, \-\-service \fIURL\fR
Service URL.
.TP
.B \-t, \-\-type \fI{ollama,openai}\fR
Service type, default is ollama.
.TP
.B \-m, \-\-model \fIMODEL\fR
Model name. If omitted, BookGen auto-discovers a current model.
.TP
.B \-C, \-\-context \fISIZE\fR
Context size.
.TP
.B \-o, \-\-outdir \fIPATH\fR
Output directory.
.TP
.B \-s, \-\-summary-size \fINUM\fR
Summary target size in words.
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-chapter \fINUM|N..M\fR
Chapter range.
.TP
.B \-c, \-\-chapter-format \fISPEC\fR
Chapter title format containing %d, such as "第%d章".
.TP
.B \-l, \-\-lang \fILANG\fR
Output language.
.TP
.B \-e, \-\-echo
Echo generated chapter text to stdout while writing files.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-verbose
Increase verbosity (repeatable).
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quiet
Decrease verbosity (repeatable).
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print version and exit.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Show help and exit.
